# Release Packaging Policy

Every GitHub Release for this project **must** ship as a pair of signed-style
Inno Setup Windows installers (`.exe`), one per UI language. **Never** upload
zip archives, loose PyInstaller folders, or raw executables as release assets.

## Required assets per release

Exactly two files, both produced by `installer.iss` via the `release.yml`
workflow:

| Language | Upload filename (ASCII-safe, used on GitHub) | Installed product name |
|----------|----------------------------------------------|------------------------|
| zh-CN    | `PPT-Voice-Control-zh-CN-Setup-v<version>.exe` | `PPT语音控制助手` (wizard + shortcuts in Chinese) |
| en-US    | `PPT-Voice-Control-en-US-Setup-v<version>.exe` | `PPT Voice Control` (English wizard) |

> GitHub's Release API sanitizes non-ASCII filenames to dots, so the uploaded
> asset name is ASCII on purpose. The installer itself and all installed
> artifacts (shortcuts, install dir, window title) remain localized.

## How to cut a release

1. Commit all changes to `main` and push.
2. Create an annotated tag `vX.Y.Z` (semantic version — patch for bugfixes,
   minor for features, major for breaking changes).
3. Push the tag: `git push origin vX.Y.Z`.
4. The `release.yml` workflow runs a matrix build (zh + en), installs
   Inno Setup 6 (plus `ChineseSimplified.isl`), compiles `installer.iss`
   for each language, renames the zh asset to the ASCII-safe name, and
   attaches both installers to the Release.
5. Verify with `gh release view vX.Y.Z --json assets` — you should see
   **exactly two `.exe` files**, nothing else.

## Do not

- Do not add a zip / tar / 7z job to `release.yml`.
- Do not upload `dist/` folders or raw `.exe` from PyInstaller.
- Do not recreate the deprecated `build_installer_offline.iss`. The single
  parameterized `installer.iss` handles both languages.
- Do not push a release without bumping the tag version.
